description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity fora motivated, enthusiastic Registered nurse to join our extensive Orthopaedic outpatients department at the RD&amp;E Foundation Trust Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently hold multiple sub specialty clinics each day including Hip, Knee, Foot and Ankle, Shoulder, Spinal, Rheumatology and Hand specialists. We have Physiotherapy and Occupational therapists within the department in addition to specialistpractitioners and Radiographers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our department prides itself on offering high quality outpatient care which treats the patient holistically. We currently offer a service where patients are provided with all appropriate treatment in one visit where possible, and this includes conducting initial health assessments when patients are listed for surgery. We also strongly promote patients achieving optimum health particularly in relation to those who are listed for surgery in order to maximize patient outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe in acting on patient feedback and ensuring that where possible suitable changes are implemented.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The registered nurse successful in gaining this position will be expected to ensure that standards of care are upheld within the department, and act as a positive role model to all junior staffincluding nursing students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is for 0.64 WTE (24 hours per week).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness,&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
